President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation on World Intellectual Property Day, emphasizing the importance of protecting and securing intellectual property rights. He acknowledges the historical role of intellectual property in driving economic growth and human development in the United States. The proclamation highlights the significant contribution of intellectual property-intensive industries to employment and the country's gross domestic product. President Trump mentions the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA) and an executive order aimed at protecting intellectual property rights holders from counterfeit and pirated goods online. He also recognizes the importance of intellectual property in the ongoing battle against the coronavirus, as industries rely on strong intellectual property protections to develop new tools and treatments. The proclamation concludes by encouraging Americans to observe World Intellectual Property Day and celebrate the benefits of intellectual property to the economy and the country.